OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJapan urges 37 million     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpeople to switch off lights
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Japan's government has urged people in 
OL,6, Tokyo and its surrounding area to use  
OL,7, less electricity on Monday, as it      
OL,8, warned that supplies will be strained  
OL,9, as the country faces a heatwave.       
OL,11,FThe Ministry of Economy, Trade and     
OL,12,FIndustry expects demand for power to be
OL,13,F"severe" this afternoon local time.    
OL,15,FIt said people should switch off       
OL,16,Funnecessary lights but still use air   
OL,17,Fconditioning to avoid heatstroke.      
OL,19,FFor weeks, officials have warned of a  
OL,20,Fpower crunch as temperatures rise.     
